The paper is a systematic literature review on the effects of time pressure in software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of time pressure on productivity and quality, which could be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) categories. The paper also mentions the causes of time pressure, which could be relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Cryptography (cs.CR) categories.
